text: Alisha and its variant spelling Alysha are cognates of the female given name Alicia, a variant of Alice, which comes from the Old English name Æthelhādas or Æðelhādas, meaning "noble natured" (noble of kind).https://en.m.wiktionary.org/wiki/æþele#Old_Englishhttps://en.m.wiktionary.org/wiki/-had ==Notable people with this name== * Alisha (singer), American singer * Alisha Boe (born 1997), Norwegian actress * Alisha Chinai (born 1965), Indian pop singer * Alysha Clark (born 1987), American-Israeli basketball player * Alesha Dixon, English singer ==See also== * Alicia (given name) * Elisha (given name) * Alisha (Alisha Chinai album), 2001 * Alisha's Attic, band ==References== Category:English feminine given names Category:Feminine given names
title: Alisha
